---
name: effect-deep-handler-state
---

# deep-handler state threading (handler arms return functions)

Regression for `v1-jvm-state-threaded-handler-codegen`: handler arms that return
lambdas thread an accumulator through `resume(())(s + n)`, and the return arm uses
it (`x + s`). The final `threaded(0)` applies the handle result as a function.
INT/JS always ran this; run-jvm now compiles + runs it too.

```scalascript
effect Cnt:
  def tick(n: Int): Unit

def prog(): Int =
  Cnt.tick(5)
  Cnt.tick(3)
  100

val threaded = handle(prog()) {
  case Cnt.tick(n, resume) => (s: Int) => resume(())(s + n)
  case Return(x) => (s: Int) => x + s
}
println(threaded(0))
```
